
.TH Oxcaml 3 "" "Odoc" "OCaml Library"
.SH Name
Oxcaml
.SH Synopsis
.sp 
.in 2
\fBModule Oxcaml\fR
.in 
.sp 
.SH Documentation
.sp 
.nf 
\f[CB]val\fR f : int \f[CB]\->\fR ('a\. \f[CB]'a\fR \f[CB]\->\fR \f[CB]'a\fR) \f[CB]\->\fR unit
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Polymorphic arguments require parentheses
.nf 
.sp 
.fi 
Unboxed types have a trailing hash '#'
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR pt = {
.br 
.ti +2
x : int;
.br 
.ti +2
y : float32#;
.br 
}
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR segment = {
.br 
.ti +2
start : pt#;
.br 
.ti +2
stop : pt#;
.br 
}
.sp 
.in 3
\fB1 Layouts\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_any
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout any\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_value_or_null
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout value_or_null\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_float64
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout float64\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_float32
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout float32\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_word
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout word\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_bits64
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout bits64\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_bits32
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout bits32\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_vec128
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout vec128\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_void
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Layout void\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB2 Kind abbreviations\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_value
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
value is the default kind, so the annotation is not rendered\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_immediate
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind abbreviation immediate\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_immediate64
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind abbreviation immediate64\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_immutable_data
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind abbreviation immutable_data\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_sync_data
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind abbreviation sync_data\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_mutable_data
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind abbreviation mutable_data\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB3 Kind annotations with modalities\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_portable
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind annotation with a modality\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_contended
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind annotation with a different modality\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_multi_mod
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind annotation with multiple modalities\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_everything
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
The everything bounds abbreviation\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB4 Kind annotations on parameterized types\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR 'a imm_param
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
A type parameter with a kind constraint\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR 'a float_param
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
A type parameter with a different kind constraint\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR ('a, 'b) multi_kind
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Multiple kind-constrained parameters\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB5 Kind annotations with with constraints\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR 'a t_with
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind annotation with a with constraint\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR 'a t_with_modalities
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind annotation with a with constraint and modalities\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB6 Kind annotations on type aliases\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_alias = int
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Has both a kind annotation and a manifest\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB7 Kind-constrained polymorphism in values\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]val\fR poly_immediate : 'a\. \f[CB]'a\fR \f[CB]\->\fR \f[CB]'a\fR
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind constraint on a polymorphic type variable\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]val\fR poly_float64 : 'a\. \f[CB]'a\fR \f[CB]\->\fR \f[CB]'a\fR
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Kind constraint on a polymorphic type variable with a different kind\.
.nf 
.sp 
.in 3
\fB8 Parenthesization of product kinds\fR
.in 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_many_modalities
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
A mod kind annotation with many modalities\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_outer_mod
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Should render as (float64 & immediate) mod portable\.
.nf 
.sp 
\f[CB]type\fR t_inner_mod
.fi 
.br 
.ti +2
Should render as float64 & (immediate mod portable)\.
.nf 

